<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870924-0169 </DOCNO><HL> Emhart Unit Gets NASA Job</HL><DD> 09/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EMH GOVMT </IN><DATELINE> FRAMINGTON, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Emhart Corp. said its Planning Research Corp. subsidiary has been awarded a $57.8 million contract from the National Aeronautics and Space Administration to work on an aeronautics and space shuttle program.    The two-year contract will enable the unit to continue work developed during a $49.2 million three-year contract that expires this month.    Emhart is a maker of hardware fasteners and machinery and owns a computer service concern. </TEXT></DOC>